1. A alone can do a piece of work in 45 days. A is 80% more efficient than B. In how many days can A and B together complete the work?
2. A is two times as efficient as B. B is three times as efficient C. If C alone can do a piece of work in 60 days, how many days are required by A, B and C together to complete the entire work?
3. A, B and D working together can do a piece of work in 5 1/3 days. A alone can do the work in 24 days. B alone can do the same work in 16 days. C is twice as efficient as D. If A, B and D work together for 4 days and then C replaces D, in how many days A, B and C together complete the remaining work?
4. A can do ¼ of a work in 10 days. B can do 1/3 of the work in 20 days. In how many days can both A and B together do the work?
5. A alone can complete 1/3 part of a work in 60 days and B alone can complete ¼ part of the same work 30 days. In how many days A and B together can complete the same work?
6. A can do 4/5 of a work in 20 days and B can do ¾ of the same work in 15 days. They work together for 10 days. C alone completes the remaining work in 1 day. B and C together can complete ¾ of the same work in?
7. A and B together can complete 1/6 of the work in 5days. B and C can complete 1/5 of the work in 8days.  A and C together can complete half of the work in 10 days. In how many days can A, B and C together complete ¼ of the work?
8. A and B can complete a work in 8days and 16days, respectively. They start work together but A leaves 4 days before the completion of the work. In how many days will the entire work be completed?
9. S, R and K alone can complete a work in 24, 30, and 20 days, respectively. They start the work together. However, 6 days and 3 days before the completion of the work S and R leave in that order. In how many days will the work be completed? 
10. P, Q, R and S alone can complete a work in 8, 12, 16 and 24 days respectively. Initially they started working together, but after 2days P and Q left. One day before the completion of the work S also left. How many days were required for completing the whole work?
11. 12 men can build a wall in 24.5days. How many men would be able to build five such walls on 49 days?
12. Working 8 hrs per day, X number of persons can build a 150m wall in 10 days. If seven more persons join them, by working 6 hrs per day they can build a 120m wall in 6 days. How many persons were there at the beginning?
13. A contractor undertakes to build a wall in 25 days. He employs 200 men for this purpose, who works for 8hrs per day. After 15days he finds that only 2/5 of the work is completed. How many additional men are required for completing the remaining work within the given time?
14. If 2men, 4 women and 3boys can do a piece of work in 8days, then in how many days can 4men, 8women and 6boys complete the same work?
15. If 6men can complete a piece of work in 18days and 12 women can do the same work in 15day, then in how many days can 9 men and 15 women complete the work?
16. 6 men and 8 women could finish a work in 14 days where as 8 men and 12 women could finish the same work in 10 days. How much time would be taken to finish the same work if one man worked alone?
